HEADWORD: Missel
<hw>Mis"sel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Mistletoe.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Missel bird</b></col>, <col><b>Missel
thrush</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a large European thrush
(<spn>Turdus viscivorus</spn>) which feeds on the berries of the
mistletoe; -- called also <altname>mistletoe thrush</altname> and
<altname>missel</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misseldine</ent>⟦br⟧
